            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Google treats a ccTLD as a strong geo-targeting signal — an .de site gets a natural boost in Google Germany. The trade-off: ranking outside that country is harder because the ccTLD is locked to one location.</p></div></div>
